Program: Outlook
Title: 05/05/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00gbjy1
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 9 May 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world: today, Jackie Katounas became one of New Zealand's most notorious criminals, thought to be so dangerous she was locked up in a tough male prison. Jackie describes finding redemption and turning her life around; also, why Connor McCrorey chases storms in America when most people are running away from them; and the Indian drag queen who is breaking taboos in his conservative home town. Show less